      • earlyElements

        public java.util.HashMap<SOCPlayerElement.PEType,java.lang.Integer> earlyElements
        PlayerElements which should be set before placing any pieces, or null. Player's other elements are set after piece placement.

        Includes these elements for scenario support: PLAYEREVENTS_BITMASK, SCENARIO_SVP_LANDAREAS_BITMASK, STARTING_LANDAREAS

        Since:

      • elements

        public java.util.HashMap<SOCPlayerElement.PEType,java.lang.Integer> elements
        Available piece counts, SVP, cloth count, hasPlayedDevCard and other flags, etc. Less common elements are omitted if 0. These elements are set after piece placement; see also earlyElements.

        Elements for scenario support: SCENARIO_SVP here, others in earlyElements.

        See SavedGameModel.MODEL_VERSION javadoc for history of what version adds which elements.

      • resRollStats

      • oldDevCards

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> oldDevCards
        Standard dev card types in player's hand, received in current turn (new) or previous turns (playable or kept until end of game). Each item is a card type like SOCDevCardConstants.ROADS, from SOCInventoryItem.itype field.

        In model schema 2.3.00, these were written as arrays of ints for dev card type constants. In 2.4.00 and higher, the dev card types in each array are written as strings ("ROADS", "UNIV", etc) from SOCDevCard.getCardTypeName(int). For compatibility, unknown types are written as integer strings ("42"), and the adapter can read both integers and strings. See SavedGameModel.DevCardEnumListAdapter code for details.

        See Also:
        playedDevCards

      • newDevCards

        public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> newDevCards
        Standard dev card types in player's hand, received in current turn (new) or previous turns (playable or kept until end of game). Each item is a card type like SOCDevCardConstants.ROADS, from SOCInventoryItem.itype field.

        In model schema 2.3.00, these were written as arrays of ints for dev card type constants. In 2.4.00 and higher, the dev card types in each array are written as strings ("ROADS", "UNIV", etc) from SOCDevCard.getCardTypeName(int). For compatibility, unknown types are written as integer strings ("42"), and the adapter can read both integers and strings. See SavedGameModel.DevCardEnumListAdapter code for details.

        See Also:
        playedDevCards

    • Method Detail

      • loadInto

        void loadInto(SOCPlayer pl)
        Load PlayerInfo fields into this SOCPlayer. If seat isn't vacant, call SOCGame.addPlayer(String, int) before calling this: Will let addPlayer(..) set player name, instead of doing so here from name, in case player has been renamed to avoid conflicts.
        Parameters:
        pl - Player object to load from PlayerInfo; not null
